into  the  Houston/Galveston  areas.  We  are  prepared,  I  think,  even 
better  prepared  for  this  one,  because  it’s  our  anticipation  of  the 
water as it rises and surges will also retreat back to the ocean and 
will  allow  us  quicker  access  back  in  whether  it’s  for  power  or  the 
restoration  of  the  towers  or  anything  else  that  is  damaged  in  the 
storm, sir. 

Mr.  CITRON.  While  we  also  employ  battery  backup  mechanisms 
as  well  as  generators  powered  by  diesel  fuel,  I  think  we  miss  the 
